{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17655797","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17655797"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T22:06:10+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T22:06:10+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18683"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18683","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18683"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11415"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76821"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11415","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11415"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18683"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62324"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"10391"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"26439"},{"type":"contributions","id":"26445"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76821","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/76821"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe cerebral hemispheres demonstrate functional lateralisation, with each side showing specialisation for different cognitive processes.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following cognitive functions is predominantly associated with the left cerebral hemisphere?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Language processing and logical reasoning","Musical appreciation","Emotional processing","Spatial awareness","Face recognition"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe left cerebral hemisphere is specialised for \u003Cstrong\u003Elanguage processing and logical reasoning\u003C/strong\u003E. It processes information in a systematic, step-by-step manner and is crucial for analytical thinking, mathematics, and contains key language areas including Broca\u0027s area (speech production) and Wernicke\u0027s area (language comprehension).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMusical appreciation\u003C/strong\u003E - While both hemispheres contribute to music processing, the right hemisphere is more involved in melody and pitch perception\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEmotional processing\u003C/strong\u003E - This is predominantly associated with the right hemisphere, particularly negative emotions\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ESpatial awareness\u003C/strong\u003E - The right hemisphere is dominant for visuospatial processing and navigation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFace recognition\u003C/strong\u003E - The right hemisphere contains specialised regions for face processing and recognition\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe left hemisphere\u0027s analytical specialisation allows for detailed, systematic processing of information, which is essential for tasks requiring logical analysis, language comprehension, and mathematical reasoning.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The left cerebral hemisphere specialises in analytical tasks, language processing, and logical reasoning.","The left hemisphere processes information sequentially and systematically rather than holistically.","Language centres (Broca\u0027s and Wernicke\u0027s areas) are typically located in the left hemisphere in most right-handed people."],"references":["Tortora GJ, Derrickson BH, Burkett B, Peoples G, Dye D, Cooke J, et al. Principles of Anatomy and Physiology, 2nd Asia-Pacific Edition: John Wiley \u0026 Sons, Limited; 2019"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62324"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18683"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"62324","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/62324"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-05T13:44:45+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-05T13:45:15+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11415"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"76821"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4930","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4930"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Nervous System","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":"2024-10-17T23:16:52+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-27T10:23:42+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"13"}},"